OL,3,CNigel Farage to compete with record 33
OL,4,Ccandidates in Clacton by-election
OL,6,FBefore his resignation, Farage was the
OL,7,Fsubject of a standards probe over a #5
OL,8,Fmillion gift he received from crypto-
OL,9,Fbillionaire Christopher Harborne
OL,10,Fbefore the general election.
OL,12,FHe was then referred to the standards
OL,13,Fcommissioner again over support he
OL,14,Freceived from his long-term associate
OL,15,FGeorge Cottrell, which reportedly
OL,16,Fincluded funding for staffing,
OL,17,Fsecurity and the use of a London
OL,18,Ftownhouse.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1784337480
OL,3,CNigel Farage to compete with record 33
OL,4,Ccandidates in Clacton by-election
OL,6,FThe Sunday Times said Cottrell
OL,7,Frecruited and paid three staff members
OL,8,Fto work on Farage's social media
OL,9,Fbefore the election and has continued
OL,10,Fto allow him to use a five-storey
OL,11,FGeorgian property he rented near
OL,12,FBuckingham Palace.
OL,14,FUnder parliamentary rules, newly
OL,15,Felected MPs must declare gifts or
OL,16,Fbenefits, including accommodation,
OL,17,Freceived 12 months before their
OL,18,Felection that relate to "parliamentary
OL,19,For political activities".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
